<h2 id="key-features">⚡ Key Features for Med Spa Operators</h2>

<h3>Automated Lead Nurture Sequences</h3>

The core value proposition: a prospect fills out your "Botox pricing" form at 11 PM. By 11:01 PM, they've received a personalized SMS with a link to book a free consultation. Over the next 14 days, they receive a carefully timed sequence of educational emails, social proof (reviews from similar patients), and scarcity triggers (limited appointments this month).

GHL's workflow builder lets you create these sequences visually, with conditional logic based on behavior. Did they open the email but not book? Trigger a different follow-up. Did they visit the pricing page three times? Alert your front desk for a personal call.

We've seen well-built nurture sequences convert 23% of cold leads into consultations — compared to the industry average of 8% for med spas using basic email tools.

<h3>Reputation Management Dashboard</h3>

Google reviews directly impact whether prospects book with you or your competitor down the street. GHL automates review requests via SMS after appointments, monitors review sites for new mentions, and provides response templates.

The platform also lets you gate negative feedback — unhappy patients get directed to a private feedback form first, giving you the chance to resolve issues before they become public reviews. This isn't about suppressing legitimate complaints; it's about service recovery.

Our operators average 4.7+ stars across Google profiles after implementing systematic review collection through GHL.

<div class="callout-blue">
<strong>Pro Tip:</strong> Set up review request sequences to fire 2 hours post-appointment — patients are still feeling good about results but haven't forgotten the experience. Include a direct Google review link (not your website) to minimize friction.
</div>

<h3>Two-Way Unified Inbox</h3>

Modern patients contact med spas via text, email, Instagram DM, Facebook Messenger, and Google Business Messages. Without consolidation, staff miss messages and leads die.

GHL's unified inbox pulls all conversations into one stream per contact. Your front desk sees a single thread showing every touchpoint — the original ad they clicked, emails they opened, texts they sent, and Instagram questions they asked. This context transforms consultation calls.

For multi-location operators, the inbox becomes essential. You can route messages by location, assign conversations to specific team members, and track response times across your organization.

<h3>Online Booking with Automated Reminders</h3>

GHL includes a full booking system with calendar sync (Google, Outlook, iCal), deposit collection, and automated reminder sequences. You can create different appointment types with varying durations, buffer times, and staff assignments.

The reminder system is where value compounds. Default sequences include:
- 48-hour SMS + email reminder
- 24-hour confirmation request (reply YES to confirm)
- 2-hour SMS with directions and parking info

No-shows dropped from 22% to 9% across our med spa clients after implementing these sequences. At an average treatment value of $400, that's significant recovered revenue.

<h3>Funnel and Landing Page Builder</h3>

The integrated page builder isn't Webflow-level, but it's sufficient for landing pages, lead magnets, and booking flows. More importantly, it's connected — leads captured on GHL pages automatically enter your CRM and trigger appropriate workflows.

Pre-built med spa templates let you launch campaigns same-day. We've used these for seasonal promotions (summer body sculpting, holiday gift cards) with strong results.

