<h2 id="alternatives">🔄 Notable Alternatives</h2>

While GoHighLevel is our top pick, these platforms deserve consideration:

<strong>Aesthetic Record:</strong> Better native HIPAA compliance and EMR integration, but weaker marketing automation. Works well paired with GHL — use AR for clinical records, GHL for marketing.

<strong>Podium:</strong> Superior for pure reputation management and webchat. Significantly more expensive for equivalent features. Best for operators who only need reviews and messaging, not full marketing automation.

<strong>Salesforce + Pardot:</strong> Enterprise-grade CRM with marketing automation for large multi-state groups. Expect $1,000+/month and significant implementation costs. Overkill for sub-10 location operations.

<strong>Keap (Infusionsoft):</strong> Mature marketing automation but dated interface and higher pricing. GHL has largely eclipsed it for service businesses.

<h2 id="implementation">🛠️ Implementation Tips from the Field</h2>

Based on deploying GHL across dozens of med spa locations, here's what accelerates success:

<strong>Week 1:</strong> Import your existing patient list, set up basic appointment reminders, and configure your Google review request workflow. These three automations alone justify the platform cost.

<strong>Week 2-3:</strong> Build your core lead nurture sequence for your highest-volume service (usually Botox or filler consultations). Start simple — 5-7 touchpoints over 14 days.

<strong>Week 4:</strong> Connect your paid advertising (Facebook, Google) to GHL landing pages with proper tracking. This gives you true cost-per-consultation data.

<strong>Ongoing:</strong> Add workflows incrementally. Reactivation campaigns for patients who haven't visited in 90 days. Birthday offers. Treatment package upgrades.

<div class="callout-blue">
<strong>Pro Tip:</strong> Don't try to automate everything at once. Start with appointment reminders and review requests — these have guaranteed ROI. Add sophistication as you learn the platform.
